dsDescriptionValue.value: This survey focuses on politics. Issues addressed include approval of President Clinton and Vice-President Gore, voting preferences in the 1996 election, the situation in Iraq, the condition of morals in the country today, influences on the economy, welfare, gun control laws, use of illegal drugs, race relations, and opinions of Bob Dole and other candidates. Demographic data include marital status, religion, party affiliation, political ideology, household composition, employment status, age , sex, education, race, and income. NOTES: This study is a tracking poll. The study was conducted each night from September 5th. In September approximately 400 respondents were interviewed each night. Throughout October and November, approximately 600 were interviewed each night. Questions con card 3 began on October 1st. The filename refers to the day after the interviewing took place. Data from September was a three-day rolling total. In October and November it was a tw0-day rolling total.
